text.tspan: Test cut a few holes to see your screws are correct gauge. so they hold but do not crack the wood.
Laser cut pedestal for DZUS mount flight simulator panels
This is the center support beam that runs under the center rail, cut it from 6mm plywood
so it does not block the screw holes from below. The rails are 8mm plywood, glue to
slots in the side walls. I use 3.5x25mm flathead wood screws and a 3d printed "dzus"
washer for authentic look, or if you do not care as much, enlarge the holes slightly and
use some torx wood screws with dark gray heads for example.
Blank dzus plates to cover the empty holes on the pedestal, cut from 3 or 4mm plywood.
6mm plywood center support beam goes under the wider center rail between the holes:
